nchanter is going to become much easier)  So not really important, but incorporating a spell timer period instead of a group buff timer would be much more effective. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub92.ezboard.com/ueqannounce.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQAnnounce</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Author</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/15/01 7:57:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Timers: What kind is most important?</span><hr size=1> Spell timers are currently &quot;generic&quot; in the form you mentioned.<br><br>When a spell timer expires it says something to the effect of:<br><br>&quot;WARNING!  'Spell Name' is about to fade in 60 seconds.&quot; (or the time you provide)<br><br>then<br><br>&quot;ALERT! 'Spell Name' should have faded by now.&quot;<br><br>then, if you don't clear it/reset it...  every 30 seconds, to a max of 2 reminders...<br><br>&quot;REMINDER! 'Spell Name' should have faded by now.&quot;<br><br>--<br><br>You know, I never thought about this for enchanters...  What an idea!<br><br>--<br><br>You *will* notice though that you will have to play with the amount of time you put in for the &quot;timer duration&quot;, as every computer is different in the time it actually takes the program to convert the text to a wav file, then initiate the playing of it -- there is a slight delay there.<br><br>I don't accomodate for it as I could never be accurate with all the machines out there.  You will have to experiment a bit. <br><br>So if a spell has a duration of say 30 seconds, and you know it takes *your* computer 7 seconds to convert/play the warning -- Put the duration at (30-7) or 23 seconds.<br><br>--<br><br>This brings up another possible issue, all timers play warnings...  Which for short/quick timers this might be a nuisance.  Give me more feedback and examples of short duration timer usage please. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=21.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=21.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=21.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.threadControl?topicID=21.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/deleteThread.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/feqannouncefrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub92.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqannouncefrm2">Announcements<option value="eqannouncefrm5">General<option value="eqannouncefrm4">Wish List<option value="eqannouncefrm3">Suppor